**What it should include (minimum):**

* TCP server handling multiple clients
* Commands: `GET`, `SET`, `DELETE`
* Thread pool or async I/O (epoll)
* In-memory storage (hash map)

**What makes it resume-worthy (this is where most people fail):**

* Persistence (append-only log)
* Replication (leader → follower)
* Basic fault handling (node down scenario)
* Benchmark (requests/sec)

**What it signals:**

> “I understand how real backend systems manage state, concurrency, and failures.”

